1
00:00:04,709 --> 00:00:10,686
Whenever we’re in the presence of someone 
who is extraordinarily qualified,

2
00:00:10,686 --> 00:00:12,964
it’s natural to feel humble—

3
00:00:12,964 --> 00:00:15,906
[Infinite Magnitude of Beauty]

4
00:00:15,906 --> 00:00:20,464
in any field, whoever it is.

5
00:00:23,558 --> 00:00:29,334
If someone is a musician, and then
they are in the presence of a great musician,

6
00:00:29,334 --> 00:00:32,453
they’ll feel humble 
and say things like,

7
00:00:34,033 --> 00:00:38,693
“I don’t even want to touch my instrument
in their presence.”

8
00:00:38,693 --> 00:00:43,361
Those kind of feelings come to them;
that’s what it means.

9
00:00:43,857 --> 00:00:47,326
And that’s just someone 
who’s relatively qualified.

10
00:00:47,379 --> 00:00:49,297
What are relative qualifications?

11
00:00:49,297 --> 00:00:54,302
Janmaiśvarya-śruta-śrībhir
edhamāna-madaḥ pumān

12
00:00:54,302 --> 00:00:58,783
naivārhaty abhidhātuḿ vai
tvām akiñchana-gocaram (SB: 1.8.26):

13
00:00:58,783 --> 00:01:06,006
janma [birth], qualified by high birth,
aiśvarya [wealth],

14
00:01:08,974 --> 00:01:15,222
education, beauty …
These kind of things.

15
00:01:16,007 --> 00:01:22,572
But, we’re told Bhagavān—we say
Bhagavān Sri Kṛṣṇa—Bhagavān says,

16
00:01:22,572 --> 00:01:27,641
“Aiśvaryasya samagrasya vīryasya
yaśasaḥ śriyaḥ

17
00:01:27,641 --> 00:01:32,560
jñāna-vairāgyayoś chaiva
ṣannāḥ bhaga itīraṇā” (Vp: 6.5.47).

18
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:37,554
Who is Bhagavān?
He who possesses all these qualities:

19
00:01:37,932 --> 00:01:43,584
wealth, opulence, beauty, knowledge,
renunciation, strength, fame

20
00:01:43,584 --> 00:01:48,718
—all of that, to an infinite degree.
And such a person,

21
00:01:48,718 --> 00:01:56,015
if you could find someone who had 
all of these qualities to the infinite degree,

22
00:01:56,015 --> 00:02:03,504
such a person would be irresistibly
charming and attractive,

23
00:02:03,736 --> 00:02:07,801
and qualified to be known as ‘Kṛṣṇa’.

24
00:02:08,676 --> 00:02:10,916
That is the meaning of ‘Kṛṣṇa’.

25
00:02:10,944 --> 00:02:13,990
‘Kṛṣ’ means
like magnetic attraction

26
00:02:13,990 --> 00:02:17,920
to the centre of all beauty,
charm, love, and sweetness.

27
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:20,945
And as I mentioned to you previously,

28
00:02:20,945 --> 00:02:24,464
it’s compared with the magnitude
of the sun’s heat and light.

29
00:02:24,464 --> 00:02:29,120
So, we think what kind of magnitude
of heat and light

30
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,343
is going on there.

31
00:02:31,641 --> 00:02:37,468
If we think in parallel,
the beauty of Kṛṣṇa,

32
00:02:37,468 --> 00:02:43,437
the charm, sweetness, seductive charm,
ability, knowledge, wealth, etc,

33
00:02:43,437 --> 00:02:50,999
then how are you going to feel
in the presence of such a personality?

34
00:02:50,999 --> 00:02:54,808
And what should be
your relationship?

35
00:02:57,069 --> 00:03:02,615
So, necessarily, 
we’ll say subordinate.

36
00:03:04,408 --> 00:03:09,355
But this is 
the magic of devotion.

37
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:13,403
To think that Supreme Infinite Being,
the Supreme Entity,

38
00:03:13,403 --> 00:03:19,642
comes under the control of 
a tiny finite soul through the power of love:

39
00:03:19,642 --> 00:03:23,162
love, affection, dedication.

